  "text": "To remove this register idle time, early register releasing has been proposed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] which puts a register back on the free-list before the commit of its redefining instruction. Although the main focus of previous work has been to increase performance, releasing registers early can also save power. This can be achieved either through the use of a smaller, more power-efficient register file, or by using a banked register file where banks can be turned off for power savings.",
